This paper discusses security risks in interconnected autonomous systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of rating systems to incentivize security investments, which is related to network security (cs.NI) and system and information theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the long-term interactions between autonomous systems, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
